  <body><![CDATA[I mostly agree with you. Even at the time of initial reading, I was very much aware that I was reading – er, how do I put it – a "fluff" of a novel. It wasn’t technically well-written, nor did it have very engaging characters, and it’s “twists” were rather juvenile and disappointing. But having said that, I will freely admit that I had a decent time going through its pages. It did hold my interest from the first page to the last one, mostly because of (how you put it) “the literary equivalent of pulling out at the moment of orgasm”. I also liked the historical background, and even though most of it was actually historically inaccurate, it did spark my interest in various issues that I was mostly unaware of in the past.]]></body>
  
